Java 17 brought modern language features, strong encapsulation, and security/performance improvements.

      Seventeen   (Switch In SeReGaTe)
🔹 1. Sealed Classes ⭐
      Sealed classes controls which other classes or interfaces may extend or implement them. This provides a way to define a closed hierarchy, which is 
      great for domain modeling, Safer inheritance hierarchies, Helpful for pattern matching. 
      example:      
            public sealed class Shape permits Circle, Square { ... }                  // Only Circle and Square can extend Shape
            public final class Circle extends Shape { ... }
            public final class Square extends Shape { ... }

🔹 2. Records ⭐
      Immutable data‑carrier classes.
      example:
        Javapublic record User(String name, int age) {}

      ✅ Auto‑generated: constructor, getters, equals(), hashCode(), toString()
      ✅ Ideal for DTOs, API models

🔹 3. Pattern Matching for instanceof
      This removes the redundant casting after checking an object's type.  
            Before (Java 11):
            if (obj instanceof String) {
                String s = (String) obj; // Manual cast
                System.out.println(s.toLowerCase());
            }

            After (Java 17):
            if (obj instanceof String s) {
                // 's' is already cast and ready to use
                System.out.println(s.toLowerCase());
            }


🔹 4. Switch Expressions
      ​The switch statement can now be used as an expression, meaning it can return a value. It also introduces the "arrow" (->) syntax, which eliminates the need for 
      break statements and prevents "fall-through" bugs.
      example:
        String result = switch (day) {
          case MON, FRI -> "Weekday";
          case SAT, SUN -> "Weekend";
          default -> {
              String res = "Midweek";
              yield res;                   // Use 'yield' to return a value from a block
          }
      };

🔹 5. Text Blocks
        Text blocks make it easy to write multi-line strings (like JSON, SQL, or HTML) without messy concatenation or escape characters.  
        example:
          String json = """
            {
              "name": "Java",
              "version": 17
            }  
            """;


🔹 6. Garbage Collector Updates
      Improved G1 GC
      ZGC & Shenandoah more mature (low‑latency)

      ✅ Better performance for large heaps


